essfully with no errors or warnings.\\n2. **API Logic Verification**: Ran `node scripts/test-project-apis.js`, which compiles the routes and exercises all of the Projects CRUD APIs (GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE, RBAC filters, search functionality, etc.). It passed with complete success.\\n\\nEverything is working beautifully and aligned with the constitutional constraints. I will now submit the final status and exit.\"}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-27T12-14-43-446Z-135-phase5-api-projects-crud-fix-2.log:165:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T12:14:42.305Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_end\",\"contentType\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I have completed the investigation and successfully resolved the issue. Here is a summary of the resolution:\\n\\n### Changes Made:\\n- **`eslint.config.mjs`**: Added `\\\"temp-project-build/**\\\"` to the `globalIgnores` list. This prevents the linter from checking generated, CommonJS-transpiled Javascript files in the temporary test build directory which contains require-based imports generated during compilation.\\n- **Cleanup**: Removed the untracked `temp-project-build/` directory from the workspace.\\n\\n### Validation Done:\\n1. **Lint Check**: Ran `npm run lint` and confirmed that it now passes successfully with no errors or warnings.\\n2. **API Logic Verification**: Ran `node scripts/test-project-apis.js`, which compiles the routes and exercises all of the Projects CRUD APIs (GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE, RBAC filters, search functionality, etc.). It passed with complete success.\\n\\nEverything is working beautifully and aligned with the constitutional constraints. I will now submit the final status and exit.\"}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-27T12-09-07-680Z-135-phase5-api-projects-crud-implement.log:176:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T12:05:23.701Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Designing Project API Tests**\\n\\nI'm now going to explore creating an automated test suite. I plan to build a custom test script, like `scripts/test-project-apis.js`, to run tests on the Projects CRUD APIs, similar to `scripts/test-user-apis.js`. This is to ensure all API logic adheres precisely to the specifications. I will start by designing the in-memory global projects store and seeding it with data from `INITIAL_PROJECTS` and `previewProjects`, mapped to corresponding client accounts like `\\\"client-001\\\"`.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-27T12-09-07-680Z-135-phase5-api-projects-crud-implement.log:186:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T12:05:41.008Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Refining Projects API Endpoints**\\n\\nI'm working on refining the projects API endpoints, focusing on implementation details. I've defined `API_MOCK_PROJECTS` in `lib/api-projects.ts` for in-memory global state, with related interface definitions, seeding logic, and helper functions. I am implementing the routes: `/app/api/v1/projects/route.ts` for listing (GET) and creating (POST), and `/app/api/v1/projects/[id]/route.ts` for fetching (GET by ID), updating (PATCH), and deleting (DELETE). Plus I'll write `scripts/test-project-apis.js` for automation. I've also noted files to avoid. I am clarifying the required interface, and plan to include the filters required.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false\n[... output truncated: 109059 chars total. Refine the command (grep, head, tail) to view the elided middle ...]\nh`, `owner`, `nodesCount`, `enclaveType`, `desc`, `lastUpdated`.\\n  - Added an in-memory database store `API_MOCK_PROJECTS` initialized globally to ensure persistence across API requests.\\n  - Added robust helper functions: `getNextProjectId()`, `getClientNameFromId()`, and `getClientIdFromAssociation()`.\\n- **`app/api/v1/projects/route.ts`** (Created):\\n  - Created the general endpoint handling `GET` (listing) and `POST` (creation).\\n  - Implemented advanced filters: `client_id` (admin-only), `phase`, `status`, `health`, `owner`, and `search` (multi-field keyword match).\\n  - Enforced strict RBAC: Admin roles can access everything, while client roles are restricted to viewing only projects matching their associated client ID.\\n- **`app/api/v1/projects/[id]/route.ts`** (Created):\\n  - Created the dynamic endpoint handling `GET` (retrieve single project), `PATCH` (update), and `DELETE` (delete).\\n  - Handled input validation for partial updates (`PATCH`), returning `400 Bad Request` on invalid inputs.\\n  - Blocked non-authorized tenants (clients querying projects of other clients) with `403 Forbidden` responses.\\n- **`scripts/test-project-apis.js`** (Created):\\n  - Built an automated integration test script that compiles and executes exhaustive test scenarios verifying authentications, filters, individual lookups, cross-tenant protection, and CRUD operations.\\n\\n### 2. Validation Performed:\\n- Executed `scripts/test-project-apis.js` locally. The verification suite successfully passed all tests:\\n  - Auth/status checks (active/inactive user gates and Bearer tokens checks) are fully functional.\\n  - Multi-tenant list scoping filters projects exactly by `client_id` (e.g., Sarah Jenkins only gets `client-004`).\\n  - Search keyword queries find appropriate target fields.\\n  - Individual retrieval validates both successful lookups and cross-tenant `403 Forbidden` boundaries.\\n  - Project creation is blocked for client roles but successfully provisions and maps client names for admin users.\\n  - Project modifications (`PATCH`) and deletions (`DELETE`) correctly update/remove states inside global database memory.\\n- Executed existing verification suites (`test-user-apis.js` and `verify-auth-endpoints.js`) to guarantee zero regressions. All tests are perfectly green!\\n\\n### 3. Limitations:\\n- Standard Next.js server-side memory persistence is utilized for mock DB storage as database engines are excluded per project 